Samsung launched its Galaxy S20 smartphones earlier this month. The range comprises three devices – the Galaxy S20, S20+, and S20 Ultra. These devices have OLED displays ranging from 6.2- to 6.9-inches, all of which offer 120Hz refresh rates. The flagship S20 Ultra also sports a quadruple-lens primary camera system that boasts up to 100x Super Resolution Zoom. Each device will also use Samsung’s latest flagship processor – the Exynos 990. The prepaid pricing for these devices is as follows: The smartphones will launch on 6 March 2020 and are currently available for pre-order. Customers who pre-order or purchase the S20+ or S20 Ultra before 12 March will also receive a free pair of Galaxy Buds+. We have listed the best contract deals for the new Galaxy S20 range in South Africa below. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-338384" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Galaxy-S20-640x430.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Galaxy-S20.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Galaxy-S20-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Galaxy-S20-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-338382" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Galaxy-S20-Plus-640x430.jpg" alt="Galaxy S20 Plus" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Galaxy-S20-Plus.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Galaxy-S20-Plus-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Galaxy-S20-Plus-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-338380" src="https://mybro